HEADWORD: Laughingstock
<hw>Laugh"ing*stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An object of
ridicule; a butt of sport.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When he talked, he talked nonsense, and made himself the
<qex>laughingstock</qex> of his hearers.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laughsome</ent>⟦br⟧
